<h4>Sea to Sky School District</h4>
<p>The beautiful Sea to Sky school district is located just north of Vancouver encompassing the three small towns of Squamish, Pemberton, and the host of the 2010 Olympics, Whistler.  Sea to Sky offers a great range of school sizes and community lifestyles to choose from.  All four schools have libraries, computer laboratories, gymnasiums, art, band, theatre and fully operational science labs. The international students are also given many opportunities to take field trips on the weekends and holidays. They have group days at the mountains, hiking and kayaking adventures, and even get to go visit the big city (Vancouver).  </p>

<p class="redText"><strong><a href="BCschools/whistler.cfm" class="redLink">Whistler Secondary</a>  |  <a href="BCschools/pemberton.cfm" class="redLink">Pemberton Secondary</a>  |  <a href="BCschools/howe.cfm" class="redLink">Howe Sound Secondary</a></strong></p>
<br />
<hr />
<br />
<h4>Rocky Mountain School District</h4>
<p>Located within Canada's famous Rocky Mountains, the Rocky Mountain school district has been hosting international students since 1987. The district consists of three towns (population), Kimberley (7000), Invermere (3000), and Golden (3000). This area is great for students who truly love the outdoors.  Each of the three high schools is located in a resort community with a world-class ski resort. In the summer, the ski resorts transform into a paradise for any person that enjoys mountain biking, hiking and golfing. Many sport and hobby specific programs such as Outdoor education, Ski patrol, equine studies, hockey academy, and soccer academy are offered as well.  The Rocky Mountain school district also offers a great weekend activity program at no additional cost to all its international students. Some of the events include: white water rafting, learn to ski and snowboard, and weekend trips away to Banff, Jasper, Calgary, and Edmonton.</p>

